Severe weather warnings were issued on Sunday . 
  It is the worst storm to hit the NSW coast in a decade . 
  The Bureau of Meteorology said the storm was expected to hit between Port Macquarie and Newcastle . 
  But it turned out to hit closer to Newcastle than expected . 
  The East Coast Low is the longest lasting weather system to hit NSW since 2007 . 
  Emergency services said they were shocked by the severity of the storm . 
  Climate specialist Don White said there was no warning system in place . 
  He said it is difficult to forecast the storm because of budget cuts . 
 